        <abstract>
            <p>Has at last received first letter CGE wrote.</p>
            <p>More specimens being sent.</p> 
<p>Sends his sketch of paper ["Fine dust in the Atlantic Ocean" (1846), <hi rend="italic">Collected papers</hi> 1: 199–203].</p> 
            <p>D’Orbigny considers Pampas clay deposit result of debacle. CD cannot doubt it is slow, estuary deposit. Would be grateful for information on this point.</p>
        </abstract>
